article.description:
Sheryl Swoopes scored 25 points as the Houston Comets earned their franchise record-tying 12th straight home
victory with a 69-62 win Saturday night over the Orlando Miracle.
article.headline: Comets tie franchise record for consecutive home wins
article.linkText: Comets beat Miracle for 12th straight home victory
article.story:
HOUSTON (AP) -- Sheryl Swoopes scored 25 points as the Houston
Comets earned their franchise record-tying 12th straight home
victory with a 69-62 win Saturday night over the Orlando Miracle.

	   Tina Thompson added 17 points and seven rebounds, and Sonja
Henning pulled down a career-high nine rebounds as Houston (21-7)
remained just one half-game behind the Los Angeles Sparks in the
Western Conference.

	   "I wanted the ball down the stretch, but so did Tina,'' Swoopes
said. "We did a really good job of recognizing that and getting
the ball to where we needed it to be. When we get open, we're hard
to beat.''

	   The Comets also won 12 straight home games during the 1999
season.

	   "We hit some really big shots,'' Henning said. "Tina hit some
big shots and Sheryl was big down the stretch. It was just a great
overall team win for us.''

	   Katie Douglas scored 18 points for the Miracle (13-14), who had
their three-game winning streak snapped. Orlando still holds the
fourth and final playoff spot in the Eastern Conference, leading
Miami by 1½ games.

	   "It was just one of those nights,'' said guard Shannon Johnson
who made just 3 of 19 shots from the floor. "I couldn't put a rock
in the ocean. But to their credit, they played good defense and we
just couldn't hit any open shots down the stretch.''

	   After a layup by Nykesha Sales got the Miracle within 63-62,
Swoopes scored the game's final six points -- four from the
free-throw line.
